claim.claim-text:
A compound represented by formula I:

or a pharmaceutically acceptable salt thereof, wherein:
AR represents phenyl or naphthyl;
HETCy represents a pyrrolidinyl or piperidinyl group;

one or two R groups are present and are selected from the group consisting of: halo, hydroxy, C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3, OC1-6 alkyl(Rq)3, CN, NH2, CO2H, CF3, NO2 and SO2NH2; one or two R' groups are present and are selected from the group consisting of C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3, OC1-6 alkyl(Rq)3, CN and NO2;
RX represents H, C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3, OC1-6 alkyl(Rq)3 or C(O)C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3;

each R" independently represents a member selected from the group consisting of: halo; hydroxy; C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3; OC1-6 alkyl(Rq)3; C3-8 cycloalkyl(Rq)3; CN; CONH2; CONHC1-6 alkyl(Rq)3; CON(C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3)2; NH2; NHC1-6 alkyl(Rq)3; N(C1-6 alkyl(RQ)3)2; CO2H; CO2C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3; C(O)C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3; aryl(Rq)3; heteroaryl(Rq)3; CF3; SH; NO2; SOyC1-6 alkyl(Rq)3, with y equal to 0, 1 or 2; SO2NH2; SO2NHC1-6 alkyl(Rq)3; SO2N(C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3)2 ; NHSO2C1-6alkyl(Rq)3, NHSO2aryl(Rq)3, NHSO2heteroary(Rq)3, N(Rq')C(O)C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3; NRq'C(O)NH(C1-6 alkyl(Rq)3); C2-4 alkenyl(Rq)2-3 and C2-4 alkynyl(Rq)1-3;
Rq represents Rq', CN, CO2H, NH(Rq"),

Rq' represents H, C1-4 alkyl, OH or phenyl;
Rq" represents H or OH;

represents phthalidyl or saccharinyl, and

represents piperidinyl.
wherein aryl refers to aromatic rings and fused ring systems which contain at least one ring having at least 6 atoms, with up to two such rings being present, containing up to 10 atoms therein, with alternating double bonds between adjacent carbon atoms;

and wherein heteroaryl refers to a monocyclic aromatic hydrocarbon group having 5 or 6 ring atoms, or a bicyclic aromatic group having 8 to 10 atoms, containing at least one heteroatom, O, S or N, in which a carbon or nitrogen atom is the point of attachment, and in which one additional carbon atom is optionally replaced by a heteroatom selected from O or S, and in which from 1 to 3 additional carbon atoms are optionally replaced by nitrogen heteroatoms.

